The Colonial Pipeline Attack
    -shut down fuel delivery from the golf coast to the east coast
    -spans 5,500 miles
  -group called darkside did it
    ransomware
      -gained control of the pipeline systems and demanded a ransom in exchange that they dont do anything
      -company turned down their systems for a while 
        -gas stations raised prices
   -their systems were too old and hadn't updated, thats why it was easy to hack into because they didnt place any updated protection for their systems
       -it only took 30 lines of code to blow up a 27-ton generator
        -rapidly open and close the circut breakers to make it explode
   -they are updating their systems now to prevent a future attack
